.TH PRAXRAIL 1 "2026-07-18" "Praxrail 0.3.4" "Praxrail Manual"
.SH NAME
pxr - terminal client for the Praxrail autonomous coding runtime
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pxr
[global options] command [arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Praxrail creates, monitors, controls, verifies, reviews, and publishes coding
tasks across explicitly approved repositories. Email and Telegram provide
bounded asynchronous actions; the terminal remains authoritative.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B runtime
serve, start, stop, restart, status, logs
.TP
.B profile
list, use
.TP
.B project
create, list, show, update, archive
.TP
.B repo
add, inspect, approve, list, show, disable, remove
.TP
.B task
create, list, show, clarify, prioritize, pause, resume, cancel, retry, abandon, archive, status, watch, logs, events, attempts, costs, verification, findings, ownership, attach, shell, return, recover, diff, check, review, fix, publish, pull-request
.TP
.B channel
setup, link, verify, status, test, preference, rotate, disable, revoke
.TP
.B approval
approve, reject
.TP
.B upgrade
preflight
.TP
.B support
bundle
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
--profile, --json, --quiet, --no-color, --non-interactive, --timeout,
--model, --base-url, --api-key-env, --review-api-key-env, --dry-run, --yes,
--follow, --version, --help.
.SH SECURITY
Repository approval, publication, revocation, and destructive task operations
require explicit confirmation. Interactive shells are available only for a
local human-owned managed workspace.
.SH SEE ALSO
https://github.com/FidelCoder/Praxrail
